DPRK and China Cooperate in Economy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- An agreement on economic and technological cooperation between governments of the DPRK and China was signed at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Monday.
 Present at the signing-ceremony from the DPRK side were Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol, Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, Vice-Minister of Construction and Building Materials Industries Yun Su Ryong, Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Ryong Nam and other officials concerned, and from the Chinese side were members of the Chinese government delegation led by Wu Yi, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and vice-premier of the State Council of China, and Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agreement was inked by Rim Kyong Man and Bo Xilai, minister of Commerce of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, an agreement on establishment of joint venture enterprise between the DPRK Ministry of Foreign Trade and the Chinese Wugang Group Corporation was signed.

17th Meeting of Board of Directors of IIJI 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The 17th Meeting of the Board of Directors of the International Institute of the Juche Idea was held in Caracas of Venezuela on Sept. 29.
 Present there were Director General Vishwanath, Secretary General Kenichi Ogami, executive members and directors of the IIJI.
  Vishwanath made a report on the summing up of the IIJI work after the 16th meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The IIJI has directed primary efforts to strengthening the organizations for the study of the Juche idea and thus many organizations were inaugurated, the reporter said, referring to the facts that the IIJI and other Juche idea study organizations in different countries and regions have conducted diverse activities for the study and dissemination of the Juche idea including seminars on the Juche idea, the Songun idea and politics. He called for further improving the activities for the study and dissemination of the Juche idea as required by the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stressing the need to arm the broad masses with the Juche idea, the great guiding idea of the cause of independence on the basis of the achievements and experience and have closer relations between the IIJI and Juche idea study organizations in regions and countries and strengthen mutual cooperation, he called for dynamically struggling for the victory of the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The meeting discussed and decided on the 2005-2006 working plan for positive activities to study and disseminate the Juche idea, the matter of recalling and by-electing directors of the IIJI and other issues.

Oppression upon Student Movement under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) reportedly released a statement on Oct. 7 to denounce the security authorities for frantic crackdown on the students' movement.
 The statement recalled that on Oct. 6 the security authorities issued a warrant of arrest for Song Hyo Won, chairperson of the 13th-term Hanchongryon, in connection with the struggle to remove the statue of MacArthur in Inchon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The security authorities issued a warrant of arrest, without any detailed evidence, charging that she "took the lead in the violent action", the statement said, branding it as an obvious crackdown to stamp out the students' movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that they talked about "the lead of violent action by the chairperson of Hanchongryon", not calling the conservative forces to account for committing violence on the participants in the struggle. This is, the statement said, a despicable criminal act aimed at shackling by dint of the evil law the youth and students who stood in the van of the reunification movement and turning back the trend of independent reunification provided by the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the security authorities do not want to be a criminal of history, they should immediately withdraw the issue of a warrant of arrest for the chairperson of Hanchongryon, the statement stressed.

Banquet Given on WPK Birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea hosted a banquet here Monday in celebration of the 60th anniversary of the glorious WPK.
 Present at the banquet were senior cadres of the Party, the state and the army, chairpersons of the friendly parties, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters and delegates to the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were members of a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the WPK and other congratulatory groups and visiting groups of overseas Koreans and other Koreans overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Invited there were party delegations and delegations and delegates of foreign countries, delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations, organizations for friendship and solidarity, the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, foreign diplomatic envoys here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the WPK and president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, made a speech at the banquet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the foundation of the WPK by President &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Kim Il Sung 60 years ago was a historic event which brought a fundamental turn in the development of the Korean revolution and the political life of the Korean people and opened up a new era of building a revolutionary party of Juche type. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung pioneered the original path of building a revolutionary party and strengthened the WPK into a powerful guiding force of the socialist cause which is successfully realizing the popular masses' ideal of independence with its high revolutionary spirit, organization and tested leadership ability, the speaker noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary feats of Kim Il Sung who built the WPK into the revolutionary party of Juche type with his outstanding idea and leadership and ushered in a great heyday of national prosperity and development will be immortal as the eternal treasure which guarantees the victory of the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the outstanding and energetic leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK could be strengthened into the glorious party of Kim Il Sung, a revolutionary and militant party remaining loyal to the idea and cause of the leader who founded the party despite the world-wide anti-socialist storms, and persistently advanced the socialist cause of Juche to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal feats of Kim Jong Il will shine forever with the invincible future of the Party and Songun Korea as he has wisely led the Juche cause of party building for over 40 years to strengthen it into the party of Kim Il Sung, the invincible vanguard for the accomplishment of the socialist cause.
 The WPK led by Kim Jong Il who has led the socialist cause of Juche to victory century after century, breaking through the rough storms of history will be always invincible and only victory and glory is always in store for the Korean people advancing under the leadership of the Party.

World Conference on Anti-Imperialist Cause of Independence in 21st Century Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The World Conference on the Anti-Imperialist Cause of Independence in the 21st Century was held in grand style in Caracas from Sept. 30 to Oct. 1.
 Attending it were a delegation of the Korean Social Scientists Society headed by Vice-President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Yang Hyong Sop who is chairman of the society, leading members of the international and regional organizations for the study of the Juche idea, delegations and delegates from two international bodies and at least 40 countries and officials of the government and political parties of Venezuela.
 Congratulatory speeches were made by the vice-minister of Higher Education of Venezuela who is president of Bolivar University, the director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, the head of the delegation of the Korean Social Scientists Society and the vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of Venezuela. Introduced at the conference was a congratulatory letter sent to the conference by the general secretary of the C.C., the All-Union Bolshevik Communist Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the plenary session Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli, deputy director general of the IIJI, made a report under the title "Let's make the 21st century a century of brilliant victory of the anti-imperialist cause of independence". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-imperialist independence is the intrinsic desire of the popular masses and a basic orientation of developing history, the reporter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A more dynamic struggle for independence against imperialism is now most urgently required for shattering the imperialists' moves for aggression and war and defending world peace and stability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Globalization" pursued by U.S. imperialism is neo-colonialism of contemporary form aimed at subjugating all the countries and the nations and assimilating them to it, the reporter noted, calling on them to be aware well of the danger and hypocritical nature of the imperialists' moves for aggression committed under the pretext of "freedom" and "democracy" and conduct a dynamic campaign to disclose and shatter them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The victorious advance of the anti-imperialist cause for independence at present is unthinkable without the Songun idea based on the Juche idea, he said, noting that the Juche idea and the Songun idea serve as a bright torch clearly indicating the road of victory in the anti-imperialist cause for independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to a series of tasks to be fulfilled to bring earlier the victory of this cause, he called upon every country and nation to launch an uncompromising struggle against imperialism and boost the solidarity and cooperation among all the anti-imperialist independent forces from a firm anti-imperialist independent stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to intensify the activities for the study and dissemination of the Juche idea, he said, adding that these activities should be conducted to suit the specific historic conditions, characters and cultural traditions of every country and region and orient them to settling the realistic matters arising in accomplishing the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 30 persons including the secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, the director general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, the vice-chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, the chairman of the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and the secretary general of the African Regional Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea spoke at the plenary session.
 The people of all countries that love independence and peace should resolutely stand up against the hegemony and arbitrary practices of the U.S. imperialists, the speakers said, stressing the need to wage a powerful anti-imperialist struggle for independence, fully confident that if they fight against the U.S. imperialists to the last, they are sure to win. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers expressed firm solidarity with the Korean people in their cause of the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea.
 A declaration adopted at the conference said that it is the unanimous aspiration and historic task of humankind in the 21st century to build an independent, peaceful, friendly new world and the Juche idea and the Songun idea serve as a treasured sword for winning a certain victory in the anti-imperialist cause of independence in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration urged all the countries and nations not to get scared by the bluffing of the U.S.-led imperialists nor pin any hope for their "aid" or "remedy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the countries and nations advocating independence should firmly preserve the Juche character and national identity and settle problems arising in all fields including politics, economy, military and foreign affairs their own way, it noted, underscoring the need to boost the international unity and solidarity among the anti-imperialist independent forces and intensify the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and the Songun idea.
 A letter to leader Kim Jong Il was adopted at the conference.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from World Conference 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a letter from the participants in the World Conference on Anti-Imperialist Cause of Independence in the 21st Century.
 Kim Jong Il defined the Songun policy as the basic political mode of socialism from a new angle and has embodied it in an all-round way, thus performing the undying and historic feats for the development of the progressive idea of humankind and the human cause of independence, the letter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The might of Juche Korea, which has imposingly risen up as the invincible fortress of socialism under the banner of Songun to be admired by the world people, is now greatly encouraging all the progressive and anti-imperialist peoples of the world.
 The DPRK is displaying its dignity while resolutely maintaining its independent stand despite any threat and blackmail of the U.S. imperialists and their moves to stifle it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will further deepen the work for the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and conduct the work for applying it in keeping with regional characters and the specific conditions of countries on a higher stage, thus making positive contributions to the independent development of countries and nations and the cause of global independence.

Reception Given for Presidential Envoy to Far East Region of Russia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government hosted a reception for Konstantin Borisovich Pulikovski, presidential envoy to the Far East Region of the Russian Federation, and his party participating in the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Monday.
 Present there on invitation were Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov and staff members of the Russian embassy.
 On hand were Pak Pong Ju, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, Kim Kwang Rin, chairman of the State Planning Commission, Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Pong Ju, speaking at the reception, said that the DPRK-Russia friendly relations are developing on good terms day by day under the particular concern of the top leaders of the two countries. It is the consistent stand of the WPK and the DPRK government to continue to expand and develop the DPRK-Russia friendly and cooperative relations with a long history of friendship in various fields, he noted, adding that the Korean people sincerely wish the Russian people good success in the work to increase the national defence capability and achieve the economic growth and social stability under the leadership of President V.V. Putin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking next, the presidential envoy expressed thanks to the leadership of the DPRK for having invited them to the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the WPK and given them hospitality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He welcomed the invariable spirit of the WPK to develop the Russia-DPRK relations based on the mutual respect, equality and mutual interests, the tradition of the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russia fully supports the DPRK's efforts to ensure peace and stability and constantly achieve the social and economic development, he said, congratulating the Korean people on their achievements made in this course.

Functions Held Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks, lectures, meetings, reading-sessions, film shows and photo exhibitions were held in Brazil, India, Zimbabwe, the Czech Republic, Egypt, Sweden and Democratic Congo from Sept. 27 to Oct. 4 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 The chief of the Parliamentary Group of the Popular Socialist Party of Brazil, in a lecture, said that the WPK has made great contributions not only to the Korean revolution but to the cause of global independence over the last six decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Zimbabwean police chief in a lecture said that the WPK has been developed to be a most revolutionary and militant party and victoriously led the struggle of the Korean people for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche and building a great prosperous powerful nation under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, who has successfully carried forward the idea and cause of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Plzen City Committee of the Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia of the Czech Republic at round-table talks said as the Korean people hold the great leader in high esteem, they have confidently advanced along the road of socialism chosen by themselves without any hesitation despite the imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Youssef Amin Wali, vice-chairman of the National Democratic Party of Egypt, at round-table talks said that the WPK founded by Kim Il Sung and led by Kim Jong Il has performed great exploits by successfully leading the struggle of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rolf Hagel, chairman of the Stockholm Branch of the Communist Party of Sweden, in a lecture, said that the WPK founded by Kim Il Sung 60 years ago has its historic roots in the Down-with-Imperialism Union and is guided by the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jean Baptiste Nkoy, general secretary of the People's Rally for Socialism of Democratic Congo, at a reading-session on the "First Party Organization-Society for Rallying Comrades" in Vol. 2 of Part 1 The Anti-Japanese Revolution from Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century", highly praised the immortal exploits Kim Il Sung performed by successfully accomplishing the cause of party founding and those Kim Jong Il has performed by further strengthening the WPK into a guiding force of the Songun revolution.

Letter to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a letter from former unconverted long-term prisoners Monday.
 The foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea by President  Kim Il Sung on the basis of the anti-Japanese revolutionary traditions was a revolutionary auspicious event that gave an origin to building a socialist ruling party of Juche type and a historic event which provided a powerful engine of the Juche cause as it dynamically pushed forward the Korean revolution under the ever-victorious banner, the letter said, and went on:
 The WPK which was founded and strengthened by Kim Il Sung has firmly preserved its intrinsic nature as his party and more powerfully demonstrated its militancy and might as a guide and organizer of the Juche revolution thanks to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last 40 odd years since he has led the Party work,   Kim Jong Il has regarded it as his lifelong mission to strengthen the Party into the party of Kim Il Sung and resolutely defended and comprehensively carried forward and developed &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Kim Il Sung's Juche-oriented idea of party building and feats with his outstanding idea and leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter stressed that the greater they enjoy honor and happiness, the more deeply they will cherish the awareness that they are the members of the WPK totally dedicated to  Kim Jong Il, the destiny of the country and the nation, and devote their lives to him, in the future, too, as they have invariably made the long journey of revolution under the leadership of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il.

October Jubilee Colorfully Celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 11 (KCNA) -- The 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea which fell on October 10 was colorfully celebrated in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Working people from all walks of life visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace and statues of President 
Kim Il Sung erected on Mansu Hill and other places of the country to pay homage to him who founded the WPK and developed it to be a dignified revolutionary party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A high-profile parade of units of the three services of the Korean People's Army, the Worker-Peasant Red Guards and the Young Red Guards took place at Kim Il Sung Square in the morning in celebration of the 60th jubilee of the WPK. It fully demonstrated the might of the revolutionary armed forces of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of thousands of working people, youth and students in the capital turned out to warmly welcome the paraders who have grown up to be matchless soldiers under the leadership of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Screening of films and art performances showing the 60-year-long history of the WPK and its immortal exploits were arranged at cinemas, theaters and open-air stages in the capital and different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The refurbished recreation grounds along the Taedong and Pothong Rivers, on Mt. Taesong and Moran Hill and other recreation parks in the capital and local areas were crowded with holiday-makers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As dusk was falling, there were an evening gala and torchlight procession of youth and students celebrating the jubilee at Kim Il Sung Square.
 All the celebration events strikingly demonstrated the single-minded unity between the great Party and the popular masses and the people's absolute trust in the Party.

Velada y marcha con antorchas de jovenes y estudiantes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, 11 de octubre (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar el dia 10 por la noche en la Plaza Kim Il Sung una solemne velada y marcha con antorchas de jovenes y estudiantes en celebracion del sexagenario de la fundacion del glorioso Partido del Trabajo de Corea.
�@La plaza se adorno hermosamente por las salvas tirantes y aspectos jubilosos de los bailantes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@A compas de las melodias alegres, los jovenes y estudiantes bailaron con el orgullo y optimismo de ser continuadores de Corea del Songun (priorizacion militar) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, hizo su aparicion en la tribuna de la plaza. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tambien ocuparon asientos de la tribuna los cuadros del Partido, el Estado y el ejercito, So Man Sul, presidente del Presidium del Comite Central de la Asociacion General de Coreanos Residentes en Japon (Chongryon), Wu Yi, miembro del Buro Politico del CC del Partido Comunista de China y viceprimera ministra del Consejo de Estado de la Republica Popular China, y Konstantin Borisovich Pulikovski, delegado plenipotenciario del Presidente en la zona federal del Lejano Oriente de la Federacion Rusa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En medio de la interpretacion solemne de la cancion "Somos continuadores de la revolucion", comenzo la marcha con antorchas de los vanguardias juveniles bajo el lema de "El invencible Partido del Trabajo de Corea que ha salido victorioso siguiendo a la gran bandera del Songun", poniendo en la delantera la bandera de la Union de la Juventud Socialista Kim Il Sung con la efigie de este. ? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Las filas de marcha describieron con las antorchas la insignia del PTC, la maqueta del monte Paektu, la bandera roja, etc. 
�@Con la unanime decision de todos los jovenes y estudiantes del pais de apoyar con toda fidelidad la direccion del Songun del gran partido, pasaron por la plaza inscribiendo con las antorchas las letras    "Kim Il Sung", "Kim Jong Il", "Idea Juche", "Partido del Trabajo de Corea", "Politica de Songun", "Unidad monolitica", "Gran potencia prospera", etc. y agitando las banderas del PTC y de la Union de la Juventud y las banderas rojas. 
�@El Dirigente respondio con la mano alzada a las entusiastas aclamaciones de vanguardias juveniles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Aprecio altamente y dio agradecimiento a los participantes en esta marcha quienes manifestaron bien la voluntad revolucionaria y el impetu inflexible de vanguardias juveniles de continuar con firmeza el largo camino de la Revolucion del Songun bajo la direccion del partido enarbolando siempre la antorcha para llevar a feliz termino la causa del Juche.
